<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Available material is limited but suggests a temperate East Asian distribution. Russian specimens represent rather small basidiocarps that were collected from thin, fallen angiosperm branches. The holotype from Japan is a sturdier basidiocarp that was probably growing on a thick branch or a log.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
